DataElement.preferredName: Person Interest Pregnancy Within One Year Occurrence Ind
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A response used to determine whether a person is interested in becoming pregnant within one year of an event.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Person Interest Pregnancy Within One Year Occurrence
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A human being._A state of curiosity or concern about or attention to something._The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth._On the inside; contained in._The smallest natural number and quantity it denotes: a single entity, unit, or object._A period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun, approximately 365 days; a specific one year period._An instance of something happening, such as an event or incident.

Concepts.definition: A state of curiosity or concern about or attention to something.
The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth.
The smallest natural number and quantity it denotes: a single entity, unit, or object.
A period of time that it takes for Earth to make a complete revolution around the sun, approximately 365 days; a specific one year period.
An instance of something happening, such as an event or incident.
